Package jdrasil.algorithms.upperbounds

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    GreedyPathDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    Computes greedily a path decomposition by adding vertices to the current bag that allow to quickly remove vertices from the bag again.
    GreedyPermutationDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class implements greedy permutation heuristics to compute a tree-decomposition.
    LocalSearchDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class implements a tabu search on the space of elimination orders developed by Clautiax, Moukrim, Negre and Carlier in their work "Heuristic and Metaheuristic Method for Computing Graph Treewidth".
    MaximumCardinalitySearchDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    This class implements the Maximum-Cardinality Search heuristic.
    PaceGreedyDegreeDecomposer  
    StochasticGreedyPermutationDecomposer<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
    The Greedy-Permutation heuristic performs very well and can be seen as randomized algorithm as it breaks ties randomly.
